  return a + b;
}
console.log(add(3, 7));
```

questions.explanation:
JavaScript uses the **`function`** keyword to declare a function:
```js
function greet(name) {
  // code
}
```
`def` is Python, `func` is Go/Swift, and `void` is Java/C++.

questions.text:
How many times does this loop run?
```js
for (let i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}
```

What does this code print?
```js
const dishes = ["Pizza", "Pasta", "Salad"];
for (const dish of dishes) {
  console.log(dish);
}
```

What does this function print when called with no argument?
```js
function greet(name = "stranger") {
  console.log("Hello " + name);
}
greet();
```

What does this code print?
```js
